doc_summary_long: A girl stabbed a boy at a school in Washington, D.C., Tuesday afternoon, according to the Metropolitan Police Department. The daughter of a diplomat stabbed the 13-year-old boy twice in the shoulder with scissors in Georgetown at the British International School of Washington at 2001 Wisconsin Ave. NW just before 1 p.m., police said. The victim was taken to Children's National Medical Center. He was conscious and alert and is expected to be OK.
doc_summary_short: A girl stabbed a boy at a school in Washington, D.C., Tuesday afternoon, according to the Metropolitan Police Department.
doc_title: Daughter of Diplomat Stabs Boy at British International School of Washington
